## New findings (if any)
- [MED] `src/polaris_graph/audit_ir/decision_aggregates.py:160` — `compute_aggregates()` strips `workspace_id` before querying phase 1, but the phase 1 store persists workspace IDs verbatim. That makes valid rows written under padded IDs like `'  ws1  '` invisible to aggregation and silently returns zero counts; the returned dataclass also echoes `'ws1'`, which masks the mismatch. I reproduced this directly against a workspace-local SQLite file.

## Final word
